    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NULL pointer dereference in oai_nfapi_nr_rx_data_indication\n\n### Summary\nWhen calling `oai_nfapi_nr_rx_data_indication()` the function may crash with a segmentation fault if the global `p7_config_g` pointer is not yet initialized. This occurs when the function is called before the PNF P7 configuration is fully established during startup.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_pnf.c`: Added NULL pointer checks for `p7_config_g` in all NFAPI indication functions\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_pnf.c`: Added proper error logging when configuration is not ready\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_pnf.c`: Return -1 instead of crashing when configuration is NULL\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Start OAI gNB in NFAPI mode\n2. Trigger an uplink data reception before P7 configuration is complete\n3. Observe segmentation fault in `oai_nfapi_nr_rx_data_indication()`\n\nThe crash occurs because the function attempts to use the uninitialized `p7_config_g` pointer directly without checking if it's valid first. With this fix, the function will now log an error message and return -1, allowing the calling code to handle the error gracefully.\n"
}